that are making a new high

00:53:08.280 --> 00:53:11.010
and they have a list of stocks
that are making a new low.

00:53:11.010 --> 00:53:13.550
And when I started out in
the business every day,

00:53:13.550 --> 00:53:16.800
I looked first at
the new low list.

00:53:16.800 --> 00:53:18.590
I think, what's on sale?

00:53:18.590 --> 00:53:20.595
What can we get a deal on here?

00:53:20.595 --> 00:53:22.720
And I really didn't even
look at the new high list,

00:53:22.720 --> 00:53:24.840
because I figured
if I own something

00:53:24.840 --> 00:53:27.099
and it was making a
new high, I knew that.

00:53:27.099 --> 00:53:29.140
I didn't need it to be on
a list to tell me that.

00:53:29.140 --> 00:53:31.930
I knew it, because
I'd already owned it.

00:53:31.930 --> 00:53:35.140
These days, I look
at the new high list

00:53:35.140 --> 00:53:37.930
first, and then
the new low list,

00:53:37.930 --> 00:53:40.580
because if there's something
on the new high list,

00:53:40.580 --> 00:53:41.580
there might be a reason.

00:53:41.580 --> 00:53:43.570
There might be a good reason.

00:53:43.570 --> 00:53:47.740
And if I don't own it, and
I see it making a new high,

00:53:47.740 --> 00:53:49.430
I'm more inclined
to look at that

00:53:49.430 --> 00:53:53.390
and say, what does the market
know that I don't know?

00:53:53.390 --> 00:53:54.930
